      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune non-idle stale diagnostic session states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()` only deletes entries where `state === \"idle\"` AND `queueDepth <= 0` AND `age > SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS` (30 min). Non-idle entries — such as recovery-failed sessions stuck in `\"processing\"` or `\"waiting\"` — never transition back to idle and accumulate indefinitely in the `diagnosticSessionStates` Map.\n\nThis PR adds a fallback prune condition that deletes **non-idle** stale entries exceeding the TTL. Idle entries (both queued and empty) are unaffected — idle-queued entries remain preserved for heartbeat/stuck-session recovery.\n\nFixes #91697\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts`**: In `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()`, add `else if (!isIdle && ageMs > SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS)` to prune non-idle stale entries while preserving idle queued entries for recovery. 1 file, +4 lines.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Non-idle diagnostic session state entries (recovery-failed sessions in `\"processing\"` or `\"waiting\"` state) accumulate past the 30-minute TTL. The fix prunes only non-idle stale entries, preserving idle entries with queued work for heartbeat recovery.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, openclaw commit 68e96c24ab. tsx v4.22.3.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Wrote proof script at `scripts/proof-91697.mjs` that imports `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates` and `diagnosticSessionStates` from the real production module at `src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.js`\n2. Script populates the process-local Map with 5 entries covering all state/age/queue combinations\n3. Ran `npx tsx scripts/proof-91697.mjs`\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n```\n$ npx tsx scripts/proof-91697.mjs\n\n============================================================\ndiagnostic session state prune — non-idle staleness proof\n============================================================\nnow  = 2026-06-09T12:00:00.000Z\nTTL  = 30 minutes\n\n--- Before prune ---\ntotal entries: 5\n  idle-stale-empty: state=idle queueDepth=0 age=31min\n  processing-stale: state=processing queueDepth=2 age=32min\n  waiting-stale: state=waiting queueDepth=1 age=33min\n  idle-stale-queued: state=idle queueDepth=3 age=32min\n  processing-fresh: state=processing queueDepth=2 age=10min\n\n--- After prune ---\ntotal entries: 2\n  idle-stale-queued: state=idle queueDepth=3 age=32min — PRESERVED\n  processing-fresh: state=processing queueDepth=2 age=10min — PRESERVED\n\n--- Verification ---\nidle stale empty pruned      ✓\nprocessing stale pruned      ✓\nwaiting stale pruned         ✓\nidle queued preserved        ✓\nprocessing fresh preserved   ✓\n\n✓ All checks passed.\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** 5 entries → 2 entries after prune. Non-idle stale entries (`processing-stale`, `waiting-stale`) are correctly pruned — these are the ghost entries that previously accumulated indefinitely. Idle queued entry (`idle-stale-queued`, queueDepth=3) is PRESERVED — it remains eligible for heartbeat/stuck-session recovery. Fresh entries within the TTL are unaffected. The `!isIdle` gate in the fallback ensures only non-idle entries are affected by the new condition.\n\n**What was not tested:** Gateway restart with accumulated ghost entries, interaction with `stuckSessionAbortMs` recovery path, full stuck-session recovery lifecycle.",
        "branch": "fix/91697-prune-non-idle-diagnostic-states",
